main event: Multiple UFO sightings were reported in Portland, Oregon in June 1956, including descriptions of fast-moving balls of light and strange objects circling each other in the sky.
interesting points: Witnesses reported seeing objects moving at speeds of around 1000 miles per hour, making rapid movements, and disappearing from sight.
One observation mentioned an object shaped like a cake coming to a complete stop with a single light, then moving towards Vancouver.

The report includes handwritten or typed text, and mentions an intention to obtain details and opinions through other investigative channels. No determination of validity, authenticity, or investigation results was provided.
A witness driving home from work reported seeing two strange lights in the sky approximately 4 miles west of Portland, which circled each other before rapidly moving eastward.
The report also mentioned a jet aircraft flying in the area at the time of the sighting, hinting at a possible prosaic explanation for one of the UFO sightings.
sighted object: fast-moving balls of light, strange objects circling each other in the sky
